class SlowExampleBasicUrdf:
    @skip_benchmark_if(wp.get_cuda_device_count() == 0)
    def time_load(self):
        """Time the amount of time it takes to load and run one frame of the example."""
    
        command = [
            sys.executable,
            "-m",
            "newton.examples.basic.example_basic_urdf",
            "--num-frames",
            "1",
            "--viewer",
            "null",
        ]
    
        # Run the script as a subprocess
        subprocess.run(command, capture_output=True, text=True, check=True)

    def setup(self):
        wp.build.clear_lto_cache()
        wp.build.clear_kernel_cache()

class FastInitializeModel:
    def peakmem_initialize_model_cpu(self, robot, num_worlds):
        gc.collect()
    
        with wp.ScopedDevice("cpu"):
            builder = Example.create_model_builder(robot, num_worlds, randomize=True, seed=123)
    
            # finalize model
            model = builder.finalize()
    
        del model

    def setup_cache(self):
        # Load a small model to cache the kernels
        builder = Example.create_model_builder("cartpole", 1, randomize=False, seed=123)
        model = builder.finalize(device="cpu")
        del model

class _FastBenchmark:
    def time_simulate(self):
        for _ in range(self.num_frames):
            wp.capture_launch(self.graph)
        wp.synchronize_device()

    def setup(self):
        if not hasattr(self, "builder") or self.builder is None:
            self.builder = Example.create_model_builder(
                self.robot, self.num_worlds, randomize=self.random_init, seed=123
            )
    
        self.example = Example(
            stage_path=None,
            robot=self.robot,
            randomize=self.random_init,
            headless=True,
            actuation="None",
            use_cuda_graph=True,
            builder=self.builder,
            environment=self.environment,
        )
    
        wp.synchronize_device()
    
        # Recapture the graph with control application included
        cuda_graph_comp = wp.get_device().is_cuda and wp.is_mempool_enabled(wp.get_device())
        if not cuda_graph_comp:
            raise SkipNotImplemented
        else:
            state = wp.rand_init(self.example.seed)
            with wp.ScopedCapture() as capture:
                wp.launch(
                    apply_random_control,
                    dim=(self.example.model.joint_dof_count,),
                    inputs=[state],
                    outputs=[self.example.control.joint_target],
                )
                self.example.simulate()
            self.graph = capture.graph
    
        wp.synchronize_device()
simulation.bench_mujoco.FastAllegro.time.name: simulation.bench_mujoco.FastAllegro.time_simulate

simulation.bench_viewer.FastViewerGL.tim.code:
class FastViewerGL:
    @skip_benchmark_if(wp.get_cuda_device_count() == 0)
    def time_rendering_frame(self, robot, num_worlds):
        # Rendering one frame
        self.renderer.begin_frame(0.0)
        self.renderer.log_state(self._state)
        self.renderer.end_frame()
        wp.synchronize_device()

    def setup(self, robot, num_worlds):
        wp.init()
        builder = Example.create_model_builder(robot, num_worlds, randomize=True, seed=123)
    
        # finalize model
        self._model = builder.finalize()
        self._state = self._model.state()
    
        # Setting up the renderer
        self.renderer = ViewerGL(headless=True)
        self.renderer.set_model(self._model)
simulation.bench_viewer.FastViewerGL.tim.name: simulation.bench_viewer.FastViewerGL.time_rendering_frame
